<inglise> COUNCIL REGULATION (EC) No 844/94 of 12 April 1994 amending Regulation (EEC) No 1101/89 on structural improvements in inland waterway transport </inglise>
<eesti> N&Otilde;UKOGU M&Auml;&Auml;RUS (E&Uuml;) nr 844/94, millega muudetakse m&auml;&auml;rust (EM&Uuml;) nr 1108/89 siseveetranspordi struktuurilise t&otilde;hustamise kohta </eesti>
<inglise> THE COUNCIL OF THE EUROPEAN UNION, </inglise>
<eesti> 12. aprill 1994 EUROOPA LIIDU N&Otilde;UKOGU, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community, and in particular Article 75 thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa &Uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, eriti selle artiklit 75, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the proposal from the Commission (1), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse komisjoni ettepanekut, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the opinion of the Economic and Social Committee (2), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse majandus- ja sotsiaalkomitee arvamust, </eesti>
<inglise> Acting in accordance with the procedure laid down in Article 189c of the Treaty, </inglise>
<eesti> tegutsedes asutamislepingu artiklis 189c s&auml;testatud korras, </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas Regulation (EEC) No 1101/89 (3) introduced a number of measures designed to remove the structural overcapacity in the inland waterway sector; whereas one of these measures, which is designed temporarily to curb investment in extra capacity, was initially envisaged for a five-year period; </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: m&auml;&auml;rusega (EM&Uuml;) nr 1101/89 kehtestati rida meetmeid struktuurilise &uuml;lemahutavuse likvideerimiseks siseveetranspordi sektoris; nendest meetmetest &uuml;ks, mille eesm&auml;rk on ajutiselt takistada investeerimist lisamahutavusse, n&auml;hti algselt ette viieks aastaks; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the said measures have contributed to the reduction of structural overcapacity in the inland waterway sector; whereas, however, the recent economic downturn has caused a drop in demand for inland waterway services resulting in renewed overcapacity in every sector of the inland waterway transport market; whereas it is therefore appropriate to maintain the current structural improvement measures for a certain period; whereas, movereover, the concept of a 'vessel belonging to the active fleet' should be clarified for the purposes of this Regulation; </inglise>
<eesti> nimetatud meetmed on aidanud siseveetranspordi sektori struktuurilist &uuml;lemahutavust v&auml;hendada; siiski on viimase aja majanduslangus p&otilde;hjustanud siseveetranspordi teenuste suhtes n&otilde;udluse v&auml;henemise, mis on viinud uue &uuml;lemahutavuseni k&otilde;igis siseveetranspordituru sektorites; seet&otilde;ttu on kohane j&auml;tkata kehtivate struktuurilise t&otilde;hustamise meetmete kohaldamist veel teatava ajavahemiku jooksul; k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse kohaldamiseks tuleb t&auml;psustada m&otilde;istet "aktiivsesse laevastikku kuuluv laev"; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, given that forecasts indicate that the overcapacity is likely to persist for a considerable time, it is appropriate to re-examine the situation before the end of 1996 in the light of the then existing market situation, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse prognoose &uuml;lemahutavuse j&auml;tkumise kohta veel arvestatava aja jooksul, on kohane olukord uuesti l&auml;bi vaadata enne 1996. aasta l&otilde;ppu, l&auml;htudes turu selleaegsest olukorrast, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA M&Auml;&Auml;RUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
